The All filter link carries the `selected` class, so it projects in parentheses:
`(All) Active Completed`. Selection is read from the class, not the rendered
border colour.
Pins: filter list projection with All selected.

-- dom.html --
<section class="todoapp">
	<header class="header">
		<h1>todos</h1>
		<input class="new-todo" placeholder="What needs to be done?">
	</header>
	<section class="main">
		<input id="toggle-all" class="toggle-all" type="checkbox">
		<label for="toggle-all">Mark all as complete</label>
		<ul class="todo-list">
			<li data-id="t1">
				<div class="view">
					<input class="toggle" type="checkbox">
					<label>buy milk</label>
					<button class="destroy"></button>
				</div>
				<input class="edit" value="buy milk">
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
	<footer class="footer">
		<span class="todo-count"><strong>1</strong> item left</span>
		<ul class="filters">
			<li><a class="selected" href="/">All</a></li>
			<li><a href="/active">Active</a></li>
			<li><a href="/completed">Completed</a></li>
		</ul>
	</footer>
</section>

-- projection.txt --
v > ""
#t1 [ ] buy milk
-- **1** item left | (All) Active Completed
